ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The outbreak of sleeping sickness in Angola again focuses on the breakdown
of public health in African countries plagued with civil wars. The outbreak
shows that Angola has the same resurgence of sleeping sickness as was
reported a few months ago from the Democratic Republic of Congo. Sleeping
sickness is transmitted by tsetse flies, and control rests primarily on
control of the vector. - Mod.EP
